
FileTail
  a Python class that is designed to open a file at the position of its last
  read.  It keeps its state somewhere else (in another file).


Included are two usage examples:

run1.py
  This is an example of use of FileTail class for efficient tracking recently
  added information to a text file.

run2.py
  This is an example of use of FileTail for passing information from invocation
  to invocation.
